libsignal-protocol-c
------------------------------------------
This is a ratcheting forward secrecy protocol that works in synchronous and
asynchronous messaging environments.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libcurve25519-donna1-1.3-1bl4
  libprotobuf-c-devel-1.5.2-1bl1
  libprotobuf-c1-1.5.2-1bl1
  libsignal-protocol-c-devel-2.3.3-1bl2
  libsignal-protocol-c2-2.3.3-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  check-0.15.2-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libcurve25519-donna-devel-1.3-1bl4
  libprotobuf-c-devel-1.5.2-1bl1
  libprotobuf-devel-21.12-1
  libssl-devel-3.0.19-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/signalapp/libsignal-protocol-c

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/signalapp/libsignal-protocol-c/archive/refs/tags/v2.3.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsignal-protocol-c-2.3.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsignal-protocol-c-2.3.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsignal-protocol-c-2.3.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsignal-protocol-c-2.3.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsignal-protocol-c2-2.3.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsignal-protocol-c-devel-2.3.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

